\f0\fs26 \cf0 BMI stands for Body Mass Index. It's a numerical value that is derived from a person's weight and height, and it is commonly used as a simple method to assess whether a person has a healthy body weight relative to their height. The BMI is used as a rough indicator of whether an individual is underweight, normal weight, overweight, or obese.\
\
The formula to calculate BMI is:\
\
BMI = weight (kg) / (height (m))^2\
\
Where:\
