\cf0 Based on the calculated BMI value, individuals are generally categorized into the following BMI ranges:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Underweight: BMI less than 18.5\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Normal weight: BMI 18.5 to 24.9\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Overweight: BMI 25 to 29.9\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Obesity (Class I): BMI 30 to 34.9\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Obesity (Class II): BMI 35 to 39.9\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 Obesity (Class III): BMI 40 or higher (often referred to as morbid obesity)\
